Defines the error taxonomy for ctx-status, surfaced by the runner and its callers.

All errors are validation or state failures, never panics on user input. `BadImpact` and `BadDifficulty` reject enum values outside the fixed set: "high|medium|low" and "easy|medium|hard". `StoreCorrupt` wraps JSON decode failures with the file path; `StoreNotEmpty` gates migrations to empty stores only (bootstrap, not merge). `TaskIdNotFound` fires when `delete-task` targets a nonexistent id. `Io` wraps filesystem errors with the path and cause.

Emitted by src/runner.rs and middleware that validates task payloads; no coupling to other error types in the crate.